25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Any corporate lawyers in the house?</span><hr size=1> Can I get some people to go in with me on a class action lawsuit?  I want to sue Mc Donalds, Wendy's, and several other fast food chains.  My problem is their &quot;Super Size&quot;, &quot;Biggie Size&quot;, and such policies.  I do not like the fact that in order to get the super-sized meals I am going to have to pay more for them.  In the regular-sized meals, McDonald's promises you A.) a hamburger B.) french fries C.) a beverage.  Then they turn around and promise the same thing, only more of it for more money?!  How can that be legal?  For the additional $0.49, you get A.) the same burger B.) more french fries  and C.) a bigger beverage.<br>
<br>
When are we as consumers going to get the super-sized meals for the regular price?  They are promising both customers burgers, fries, and a beverage for a price.  <br>
<br>
People who pay $10 a month for everquest get dynamic events (sometimes) and customer service.  You may not be contacted by a guide for a while after you petition, but I have yet to have a petition go unanswered for more than a day.  You get to play the game with little downtime (unless you're one of the unfortunate Prexus players).  You get everything I have seen Sony/Verant promise for $10 a month.<br>
<br>
Legends players are just playing &quot;Super-Sized&quot; EQ.  Simple as that.  Their $30 extra a month gets them more customer service, more quests, more ways to show off their spoils of victory.  They get maps, character pages, calendars of events, etc.<br>
<br>
If you want to get the Legends services, buck up and pay for them.  Otherwise keep on paying $10 a month or switch to a game that offers what you're looking for at the price you want to pay.<br>
<br>
-Gretel, 41 Druid Torv<br>
-Brauna, 25 Paladin Torv<br>
-Alfred, 19 Warrior Torv<br>
-Kalto,16 Necro Torv<br>
-Fyntyl,10 Rogue Torv<br>
