<br>
You can find the answer to your question in your First-year Contracts class. If you haven't taken Contracts yet, (and it sounds like you haven't), please check your school's credentials. The only state in the Union to continue the European civil law tradition is Lousiana, as Inkiewiz pointed out. <br>
<br>
As my Torts professor once said, you can sue anyone for anything at any time. Your cause of action would be breach of contract, but as the previous posters have said, it would be an uphill battle, and most likely expressly contradicted by the License Agreement that you &quot;sign&quot; every time you log in. <br>
<br>
A prize to any lawyers out there to figure out the origins of my name... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uanikacrystalwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anika Crystalwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/02 6:27:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22253.topic&index=28>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://216.122.250.134/html/phnxarmx2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: =)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> You can't offer SERVICEX to Consumer A, do a half-arsed job, and offer SERVICEX to Consumer B at 4x the price, call it something new, and deliver SERVICEX.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Sure you can.  Air France offers coach service from France to the US.  In the 70's, they bought a Concord.  4 times as much for a faster flight and better ammenities - the end result is the same, you're in the US, but the service and price is different.<br>
